==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by American humorist [[w:Gelett Burgess|Gelett Burgess]] (1866-1951) who, per the custom of the time, put a picture of and praise from a (ficticious) buxom young woman Miss Belinda Blurb on the dust jacket of an edition of his 1907 book ''Are you a bromide?'' distributed at a trade fair.  The name stuck for any book cover praise or material.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/blɜːb/

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# A short [[description]] of a [[book]], [[film]], or other produce written for promotional purposes.
